@startuml order-lifecycle
' ============================================================
' AlharisTech Platform — Order Processing Lifecycle Sequence
' Service Order Flow: Browse → Submit → Review → Process → Complete → Rate
' ============================================================

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif"
skinparam defaultFontSize 10

skinparam participant {
  BackgroundColor #D4E6F1
  BorderColor #2980B9
  FontColor #1A1A1A
}

skinparam actor {
  BackgroundColor #FDEBD0
  BorderColor #E67E22
  FontColor #1A1A1A
}

skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #D5F5E3
  BorderColor #27AE60
}

skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FEF9E7
  BorderColor #F1C40F
  FontSize 9
}

skinparam arrow {
  FontSize 9
}

title **AlharisTech Platform — Full Order Processing Lifecycle**
title **دورة حياة الطلب الكاملة — من التصفح إلى التقييم**

actor "Customer\nالعميل" as Customer
actor "Employee\nالموظف" as Employee
participant "Frontend\nNext.js" as Frontend
participant "Service API\nNestJS" as ServiceAPI
participant "Order Service\nDomain Logic" as OrderSvc
participant "Notification\nService" as Notify
database "PostgreSQL\norders / services" as DB
database "Object Storage\nDocument Files" as Storage

== PHASE 1: BROWSE & SELECT — تصفح واختيار الخدمة ==

Customer -> Frontend : Browse service catalog
Frontend -> ServiceAPI : GET /api/v1/services\n?category=legal-services&page=1&limit=20
ServiceAPI -> DB : SELECT * FROM services\nWHERE is_active = true\nAND category_id = ?
DB --> ServiceAPI : Paginated service list
ServiceAPI --> Frontend : 200 { data: [...services], meta: { total, page } }
Frontend --> Customer : Display service cards

Customer -> Frontend : Search for specific service
Frontend -> ServiceAPI : GET /api/v1/services\n?q=استشارة قانونية
ServiceAPI -> DB : Full-text search\nto_tsvector('arabic', name_ar || ' ' || description_ar)
DB --> ServiceAPI : Search results
ServiceAPI --> Frontend : 200 { data: [...matching services] }

Customer -> Frontend : View service detail
Frontend -> ServiceAPI : GET /api/v1/services/slug/{slug}
ServiceAPI -> DB : SELECT s.*, c.*, AVG(r.rating) as avg_rating\nFROM services s\nJOIN service_categories c\nLEFT JOIN order_ratings r
DB --> ServiceAPI : { service, category, avg_rating, total_ratings }
ServiceAPI --> Frontend : 200 { data: { ...serviceInfo, required_documents: [...] } }
Frontend --> Customer : Show full service detail with requirements

== PHASE 2: ORDER SUBMISSION — تقديم الطلب ==

Customer -> Frontend : Fill order form + upload documents
Frontend -> Frontend : Collect: notes, documents[file1, file2]

Customer -> Frontend : Submit order
Frontend -> ServiceAPI : POST /api/v1/orders\n{ serviceId, notes, documents: [...] }

ServiceAPI -> ServiceAPI : Zod validation\n· serviceId: UUID required\n· notes: max 5000 chars\n· documents: valid HTTPS URLs

ServiceAPI -> OrderSvc : submitOrder(dto, customerId)

OrderSvc -> DB : BEGIN TRANSACTION

OrderSvc -> DB : SELECT * FROM services\nWHERE id = ? AND is_active = true
DB --> OrderSvc : Service record (with required_documents)

alt Service not found or inactive
  OrderSvc --> ServiceAPI : 404 Not Found
  ServiceAPI --> Frontend : 404 { error: "Service not found" }
  Frontend --> Customer : Show error
else Service valid
  OrderSvc -> OrderSvc : Validate required documents:\nCheck all required: true docs are provided

  alt Missing required documents
    OrderSvc --> ServiceAPI : 422 { error: "ORDER_MISSING_DOCUMENTS"\n  details: { missingDocuments: [...] } }
    ServiceAPI --> Frontend : 422 Validation Error
    Frontend --> Customer : Highlight missing documents
  else All documents provided
    OrderSvc -> OrderSvc : Generate reference_number\nFormat: ORD-YYYYMMDD-XXXX

    OrderSvc -> DB : INSERT INTO orders (\n  customer_id, service_id, status: 'pending',\n  total_amount: service.price, currency: 'SAR',\n  documents: [...], notes, reference_number,\n  status_history: [{ status: 'pending', ... }])

    DB --> OrderSvc : Order created

    note right of OrderSvc
      **Status Transition:**
      NULL → pending
      triggered by: submitOrder()
    endnote

    OrderSvc -> DB : COMMIT TRANSACTION

    OrderSvc -> Notify : Publish **OrderPlaced** event\n{ orderId, customerId, serviceId,\n  referenceNumber, totalAmount }

    Notify -> Notify : 1. Customer: Order confirmation email\n2. Staff: New order alert (in-app + email)

    OrderSvc --> ServiceAPI : 201 Created
    ServiceAPI --> Frontend : 201 { data: { id, referenceNumber, status: "pending", ... } }
    Frontend --> Customer : Confirmation screen\nShow reference number
  end
end

== PHASE 3: REVIEW & CLARIFICATION — المراجعة والاستيضاح ==

note over Employee, DB
  **Manager/Admin assigns order to employee**
  Only users with role='employee' can be assigned.
  Assignment auto-transitions pending → in_review.
endnote

Employee -> ServiceAPI : GET /api/v1/orders?status=pending&assigned_to=null
ServiceAPI -> DB : SELECT * FROM orders\nWHERE status = 'pending'\nAND assigned_to IS NULL
DB --> ServiceAPI : Unassigned pending orders
ServiceAPI --> Employee : 200 { data: [...orders] }

Employee -> ServiceAPI : View order detail
ServiceAPI -> DB : SELECT * FROM orders WHERE id = ?
DB --> ServiceAPI : Full order with documents
ServiceAPI --> Employee : 200 { data: { ...order, documents, notes } }

Employee -> Employee : Review documents:\n· Check national ID validity\n· Verify case documents\n· Assess completeness

alt Documents incomplete or need clarification
  Employee -> ServiceAPI : PATCH /api/v1/orders/{id}/status\n{ status: "pending", note: "يرجى توفير عقد الملكية" }

  ServiceAPI -> OrderSvc : updateStatus(orderId, "pending", note, employeeId)

  note right of OrderSvc
    **Status Transition:**
    in_review → pending
    (return for clarification)
  endnote

  OrderSvc -> DB : BEGIN TXN\nUPDATE orders SET status = 'pending'\nAPPEND status_history entry
  DB --> OrderSvc : Updated

  OrderSvc -> Notify : Publish **OrderStatusChanged**\n{ orderId, oldStatus: in_review,\n  newStatus: pending, note: "طلب مستندات إضافية" }

  Notify -> Customer : Email: "المستندات المطلوبة غير مكتملة"\n+ link to upload portal

  OrderSvc --> ServiceAPI : 200
  ServiceAPI --> Employee : 200 OK

  Customer -> Frontend : View notification + upload missing docs
  Frontend -> ServiceAPI : POST /api/v1/orders/{id}/documents\n{ documents: [{ name, url, type }] }

  ServiceAPI -> OrderSvc : uploadDocuments(orderId, documents, customerId)

  OrderSvc -> OrderSvc : Validate:\n· File types against service.required_documents\n· File sizes (max per document)\n· Order not in terminal status

  OrderSvc -> DB : UPDATE orders\nAPPEND documents to JSONB array
  DB --> OrderSvc : Documents appended

  OrderSvc -> Notify : Publish **DocumentsUploaded**\n{ orderId, documentCount }

  OrderSvc --> ServiceAPI : 200
  ServiceAPI --> Customer : Confirmation: documents uploaded

  Customer -> ServiceAPI : Response: "تم رفع المستندات المطلوبة"

  note over Employee
    Employee notified of
    customer response.
    Resumes review.
  endnote
end

Employee -> ServiceAPI : PATCH /api/v1/orders/{id}/status\n{ status: "in_review" }
ServiceAPI -> OrderSvc : updateStatus(orderId, "in_review")

note right of OrderSvc
  **Status Transition:**
  pending → in_review
  triggered by: employee accepting order
endnote

OrderSvc -> DB : UPDATE orders SET status = 'in_review'\nAPPEND status_history
OrderSvc -> Notify : Publish **OrderStatusChanged**\n(oldStatus: pending → newStatus: in_review)
Notify -> Customer : Email: "جاري مراجعة طلبك"

== PHASE 4: PROCESSING — المعالجة ==

Employee -> Employee : All documents verified ✓
Employee -> ServiceAPI : PATCH /api/v1/orders/{id}/status\n{ status: "in_progress", note: "بدء معالجة الطلب" }

ServiceAPI -> OrderSvc : updateStatus(orderId, "in_progress")

note right of OrderSvc
  **Status Transition:**
  in_review → in_progress
  guard: all required docs verified
endnote

OrderSvc -> OrderSvc : Validate documents:\nAll required documents must be verified = true

alt Documents not verified
  OrderSvc --> ServiceAPI : 422 { error: "DOCUMENTS_NOT_VERIFIED" }
else All verified
  OrderSvc -> DB : BEGIN TXN\nUPDATE orders SET status = 'in_progress'\nAPPEND status_history
  DB --> OrderSvc : Updated

  OrderSvc -> Notify : Publish **OrderStatusChanged**\n(oldStatus: in_review → newStatus: in_progress)

  Notify -> Customer : Email: "طلبك قيد المعالجة"
  Notify -> Employee : In-app: "تم تحديث حالة الطلب"

  OrderSvc --> ServiceAPI : 200
  ServiceAPI --> Employee : 200

  loop Processing work (variable duration)
    Employee -> Employee : Perform service work\n· Legal consultation\n· Document preparation\n· Case analysis

    opt Customer requests status update
      Customer -> ServiceAPI : GET /api/v1/orders/{id}
      ServiceAPI -> DB : SELECT * FROM orders WHERE id = ?
      DB --> ServiceAPI : Current status
      ServiceAPI --> Customer : 200 { status: "in_progress", ... }
    end
  end
end

== PHASE 5: COMPLETION — إكمال الطلب ==

Employee -> ServiceAPI : PATCH /api/v1/orders/{id}/status\n{ status: "completed", note: "تم الانتهاء من الاستشارة" }

ServiceAPI -> OrderSvc : updateStatus(orderId, "completed")

note right of OrderSvc
  **Status Transition:**
  in_progress → completed (TERMINAL)
  guard: all documents verified
endnote

OrderSvc -> DB : BEGIN TXN\nUPDATE orders SET\n  status = 'completed',\n  completed_at = NOW()\nAPPEND status_history
DB --> OrderSvc : Updated

OrderSvc -> Notify : Publish **OrderCompleted**\n{ orderId, customerId, completedBy, completedAt }

Notify -> Customer : Email: "تم إكمال طلبك - يرجى التقييم"\n+ link to rating page
Notify -> Employee : In-app: "تم إكمال الطلب بنجاح"

OrderSvc --> ServiceAPI : 200
ServiceAPI --> Employee : 200 OK

== PHASE 6: RATING — التقييم ==

Customer -> Frontend : Rate the service
Frontend -> ServiceAPI : POST /api/v1/orders/{id}/rate\n{ rating: 5, comment: "خدمة ممتازة وسريعة" }

ServiceAPI -> OrderSvc : rateOrder(orderId, rating, comment, customerId)

OrderSvc -> OrderSvc : Validate:\n· Order status = 'completed'\n· Order belongs to customer\n· Not already rated\n· Rating in range 1-5

alt Validation fails
  OrderSvc --> ServiceAPI : 422 / 409 error
  ServiceAPI --> Customer : Error message
else Valid rating
  OrderSvc -> DB : UPDATE orders SET\n  rating = 5, rating_comment = '...',\n  rated_at = NOW()
  DB --> OrderSvc : Rating saved

  OrderSvc -> Notify : Publish **ServiceRated**\n{ orderId, serviceId, rating, comment }

  Notify -> Employee : In-app: "تقييم جديد: 5/5"

  OrderSvc --> ServiceAPI : 200
  ServiceAPI --> Customer : 200 { data: { rating, ratedAt } }
end

== ALTERNATIVE PATH: CANCELLATION — مسار الإلغاء ==

note over Customer, DB
  **Cancellation Path:**
  Any non-terminal status (pending, in_review, in_progress)
  can transition to cancelled with reason.
  Only Admin can reopen cancelled orders.
endnote

alt Customer requests cancellation (status = pending)
  Customer -> ServiceAPI : POST /api/v1/orders/{id}/cancel\n{ reason: "تغيرت احتياجاتي" }

  ServiceAPI -> OrderSvc : updateStatus(orderId, "cancelled", cancelReason)

  note right of OrderSvc
    **Status Transition:**
    pending → cancelled
    guard: cancel_reason required
  endnote

  OrderSvc -> DB : UPDATE orders SET\n  status = 'cancelled',\n  cancelled_at = NOW(),\n  cancel_reason = ?
  DB --> OrderSvc : Cancelled

  OrderSvc -> Notify : Publish **OrderCancelled**\n{ orderId, reason, cancelledBy }

  Notify -> Customer : Email: "تم إلغاء طلبك"
  Notify -> Employee : In-app: "تم إلغاء الطلب"

  OrderSvc --> ServiceAPI : 200
end

== TIMEOUT HANDLING — معالجة انتهاء المهلة ==

note over OrderSvc, DB
  **Order Timeout Handling:**
  · Pending orders with no employee action > 72h:
    escalate to Manager
  · In_review orders with no status change > 48h:
    notify assigned employee
  · In_progress orders exceeding estimated_duration_days:
    alert employee + manager
  · Completed orders with no rating > 14 days:
    send reminder to customer
endnote

OrderSvc -> DB : Scheduled cron: Check stale orders\nSELECT * FROM orders\nWHERE status IN ('pending','in_review','in_progress')\nAND updated_at < NOW() - INTERVAL '72 hours'

alt Stale order detected
  OrderSvc -> Notify : Publish escalation alert\n{ orderId, staleSince, currentStatus }
  Note over Notify : Escalation to Manager + assigned Employee
end

== FULL STATUS TRANSITION SUMMARY ==

note over Customer, DB
  |= From |= To |= Who |= Condition |
  | **draft** | pending | Customer | Submit complete order |
  | **pending** | in_review | Employee/System | Auto on assignment |
  | **pending** | cancelled | Customer/Admin | With cancel_reason |
  | **pending** | rejected | Employee | With rejection note |
  | **in_review** | in_progress | Employee | All docs verified |
  | **in_review** | cancelled | Admin | With cancel_reason |
  | **in_review** | rejected | Employee | With rejection note |
  | **in_review** | pending | Employee | Request more docs |
  | **in_progress** | completed | Employee | Service work done |
  | **in_progress** | cancelled | Admin | With cancel_reason |
  | **completed** | → TERMINAL | — | No further transitions |
  | **cancelled** | → TERMINAL | — | Only Admin can reopen to pending |
  | **rejected** | → TERMINAL | — | Only Admin can reopen to pending |
endnote

@enduml
